{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"veiny-trout-brink","description":"Workflow gate ops re-resolve `LLMConfig.from_env()` independently instead of receiving the caller's resolved config, producing a DOCUMENTED correctness divergence: a library caller passing an explicit non-default `config=` has it honored for the LLM calls but the workflow verdict's `model`/`runner` fields still reflect the env config (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:78-79`).\n\n## Why\nConfig resolution is a cross-cutting concern that should resolve once per run, not once per op. The current scatter silently ignores part of a caller's explicit configuration — a reliability/correctness gap for library/MCP consumers.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py:113,329`, `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_ops.py:60,104`, `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/production_batch_runner.py:89` — stop calling `LLMConfig.from_env(...)` per op.\n- Resolve `cfg` once at the run boundary (`gate_dispatch.produce_*` / `review_plan`) and pass the `runner`/`model` identity into the ops as workflow `inputs` (the pattern already used for `ticket_id`), so ops read it from `ctx.inputs` rather than re-deriving from env. Keep `StepContext` config-agnostic (`executor.py:107-120`).\n\n## Scope\nIn: single-resolution + thread model/runner identity through inputs; remove the documented divergence note. Out: redesigning `StepContext` to carry the full `LLMConfig` type.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A caller passing an explicit `config=` sees that model/runner reflected in BOTH the LLM calls and the verdict's `model`/`runner` fields.\n- [ ] No op calls `LLMConfig.from_env()` after the run boundary resolves it.\n- [ ] The divergence caveat at `plan_review/__init__.py:78-79` is removed (no longer true).\n- [ ] Existing plan-review/completion gate tests still pass.","id":"586c-bfb0-8206-4209","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":2,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Honor caller's explicit LLMConfig in workflow gate ops"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605232128463001,"uuid":"31a45b5e-b39f-41ea-8daf-aea1720e54d5"}